HEADWORD: Cephalo
<hw>Ceph"a*lo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>kefalh`</grk>
head.]</ety> <def>A combining form denoting <xex>the head</xex>, <xex>of
the head</xex>, <xex>connected with the head</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>cephalo</ex>some, <ex>cephalo</ex>pod</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

